channel.title: Connect timed out: connect
channel.description:
I've been getting this error everytime I try to connect to my server. Anyone else who tries to connect to the server get's the same error.
Here is the error in command prompt: [code]Buildfile: build.xml
runclient: [java] java.net.ConnectException: Connection timed out: connect[/code]
Here is my World.XML [code]<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?> <!DOCTYPE properties SYSTEM "http://java.sun.com/dtd/properties.dtd"> <properties> <comment>RSCD Config</comment> <entry key="version">31</entry> <entry key="ip">192.168.x.x</entry> <entry key="port">43594</entry> <entry key="name">Server Name</entry> <entry key="location">U.S.A</entry> <entry key="maxplayers">800</entry> <entry key="servernum">1</entry> <entry key="lsip">192.168.x.x</entry> <entry key="lsport">34522</entry> </properties>[/code]
Here is my ls.conf [code]<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?> <!DOCTYPE properties SYSTEM "http://java.sun.com/dtd/properties.dtd"> <properties> <comment>RSCD-LS Config</comment> <entry key="mysqlhost">rscd.mmoninjas.org</entry> <entry key="mysqldb">rscd</entry> <entry key="mysqluser">root</entry> <entry key="mysqlpass">pw-here</entry> <entry key="lsip">192.168.x.x</entry> <entry key="lsport">34522</entry> <entry key="queryip">192.168.x.x</entry> <entry key="queryport">8181</entry> </properties>[/code]
And here is my Conf.XML [code]<?xml version="1" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?> <!DOCTYPE properties SYSTEM "http://java.sun.com/dtd/properties.dtd"> <properties> <comment>Demonik Config</comment> <entry key="version">31</entry> <entry key="ip">75.173.186.xx</entry> <entry key="port">43594</entry> <entry key="name">Server Name</entry> <entry key="location">U.S</entry> <entry key="maxplayers">800</entry> <entry key="servernum">1</entry> <entry key="lsip">192.168.x.x</entry> <entry key="lsport">34522</entry> </properties>[/code]
I have my LS connect to my website so that it will load the database off of their. This shouldn't be the problem though. If you see anything wrong, please correct it.
